. These specimens were not located either in the Pic collection or in the general collection of 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[1343,1432,680,703]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">MNHN</collectionCode>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,607,2037]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,329,716,741]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">Synonyms.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[335,605,716,741]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Neobradybatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funebris">
<emphasis box="[335,605,716,741]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">Neobradybatus funebris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was described based on six specimens from 
<collectingCountry box="[1104,1153,717,740]" name="Iran" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">Iran</collectingCountry>
. There are two males and one female of a 
<taxonomicName box="[337,496,751,776]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Persexarthrus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[337,496,751,776]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">Persexarthrus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species in the Hoffmann collection (
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[916,1005,752,776]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">MNHN</collectionCode>
) labeled in a full accordance with the original description. I dissected genitalia of one male and the female. One male bears a red-printed label “ 
<collectionCode box="[1345,1421,788,812]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">
<typeStatus box="[1345,1421,788,812]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">TYPE</typeStatus>
</collectionCode>
”, two other specimens “ 
<typeStatus box="[402,550,824,848]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">PARATYPE</typeStatus>
”. Hoffmann gives a clear reference to a single 
<typeStatus box="[1084,1132,824,848]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">type</typeStatus>
specimen: “ 
<typeStatus box="[1273,1323,824,848]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">type</typeStatus>
mâle, ma collection”. In accordance with Article 
<number box="[603,662,860,884]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" value="73.1">73.1</number>
. 
<number box="[666,676,860,884]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" value="1.0">1</number>
. of the Code (
<collectionCode box="[842,909,860,884]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">ICZN</collectionCode>
<number box="[918,978,860,884]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" value="1999.0">1999</number>
), this specimen should be regarded as a 
<typeStatus box="[151,253,895,920]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">holotype</typeStatus>
. The 
<typeStatus box="[324,422,895,920]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">holotype</typeStatus>
is 
<quantity box="[467,572,895,920]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" unit="mm" value="3.5">3.50 mm</quantity>
long, completely preserved, heavily abraded and labeled “W. Laizengou 
<date box="[151,249,932,957]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" value="1961-03-14">
<number box="[151,180,932,957]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" value="14.0">14</number>
.III. 
<number box="[220,249,932,957]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" value="61.0">61</number>
</date>
<collectingCountry box="[260,328,932,956]" name="Iran" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">IRAN</collectingCountry>
G. REMAUDIERE / s 
<taxonomicName authority="Benth. &amp; Hook.f., 1865 (L.)" authorityName="Benth. &amp; Hook.f., 1865 (L.)" box="[611,740,932,957]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Rosaceae" genus="Amygdalus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Rosales" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">Amygdalus</taxonomicName>
scoparius / 
<taxonomicName box="[887,1160,932,957]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Neobradybatus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="funebris">Neobradybatus funebris</taxonomicName>
m. A. Hoffmann det. / 
<collectionCode box="[151,221,968,991]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">
<typeStatus box="[151,221,968,991]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">TYPE</typeStatus>
</collectionCode>
[red printed] / MUSEUM 
<collectionCode box="[518,595,968,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">PARIS</collectionCode>
<number box="[602,658,967,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" value="1968.0">1968</number>
Col. A. HOFFMANN / Michael Košťál reprep. 
<number box="[1197,1258,968,992]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" value="2013.0">2013</number>
”. The other two specimens with identical locality labels and red printed label “ 
<typeStatus box="[842,987,1004,1028]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">PARATYPE</typeStatus>
” should be regarded as 
<typeStatus box="[1251,1362,1005,1029]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">paratypes</typeStatus>
. In the Smreczyński collection (
<collectionCode box="[440,503,1040,1064]" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/hv18-23j2" name="Institute of Systematic Zoology" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">ISZP</collectionCode>
), there is one female with identical labeling as above and a red printed label “ 
<typeStatus box="[160,307,1076,1100]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">PARATYPE</typeStatus>
”, which should also be regarded as a 
<typeStatus box="[742,842,1077,1101]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">paratype</typeStatus>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Dieckmann" box="[854,1067,1076,1101]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" refString="Dieckmann, L. (1968) Revision der westpalaarktischen Anthonomini (Coleoptera: Curculionidae). Beitrage zur Entomologie, 17, 377 - 564." type="journal article" year="1968">
Dieckmann (
<number box="[1000,1058,1076,1101]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" value="1968.0">1968</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
saw five of six 
<typeStatus box="[1255,1303,1077,1101]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">type</typeStatus>
specimens, however referring to them as females, and found them all to be conspecific with his 
<typeStatus box="[1088,1191,1111,1136]" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">lectotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName authority="Pic. Hence, I" authorityName="Pic. Hence, I" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anthonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevispinus">
<emphasis box="[1228,1386,1111,1136]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">A. brevispinus</emphasis>
Pic. Hence, I
</taxonomicName>
have no doubt about the specific identity of 
<taxonomicName box="[746,905,1148,1173]" class="Insecta" family="Curculionidae" genus="Anthonomus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="569" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="brevispinus">
<emphasis box="[746,905,1148,1173]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="569">A. brevispinus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
